Body length 2.2–2.9. Pronotum longer than median head length. Dorsum generally
                 yellowish brown. Hemelytron with four interrupted, longitudinal, brown stripes;
                 embolium with four black spots ( Fig. 21A ).

Asia, southeastern Asia, to eastern Asia and to Australia ( Wróblewski 1972b ;
                 Nieser & Chen 1999 ; Tinerella 2008 , 2013 ; Zettel et al. 2017 ; Polhemus
                 2017 ).
